      "text": "The way forward is not to just lament supplanted skills, as Plato did, but also to recognize that as more complex skills become essential, our society must equitably educate people to develop them.  And then it always goes back to the basics.  Value people as people, not just as bundles of skills.  And that isn't something that ChatGPT can tell us how to do."
